        <blockquote>
            I personally have a bit of experience working with Omniture, Hitbox, and Google Analytics, and the idea of an open source alternative to these tools sounds very exciting. Across our network of sites, we average about 60m pageviews / month and growing, and I was wondering if that level of load is within the scope of Piwik, given the proper hardware to support it. I’d love to find a way to help the Piwik project get to the point where it could handle millions of pageviews / month. [Update 2012:  Piwik can now handle millions of pages per month!]            <small>
                <span rel="author">Jonathan</span> 
                                            </small>
        </blockquote>
    </div>        
